column1: #text=I wanted to make a chocolate cake for my niece 's birthday , so I looked through my kitchen cupboards to make sure I had all the ingredients .
#text=Luckily , my kitchen was well-stocked with baking goods .
#text=I gathered up the butter , eggs , sugar , flour , vanilla extract and cocoa .
#text=I also had a mixing bowl with a built-in electric whisk .
#text=I tossed in two sticks of butter and 2 cups of sugar and blended them together before adding the vanilla , flour and cocoa .
#text=Then I pulled a cake pan out of a drawer and greased it up with Crisco to make sure the cake would not stick .

#text=I used a spatula to spread the cake batter evenly into the dish and then , just to make the cake even tastier , I grabbed two cups of chocolate pudding out of my fridge and swirled the pudding into the cake mix .
#text=It makes for a very moist and tasty treat !
#text=I placed the cake inside the oven and cooked it at 350 degrees for 45 minute .
#text=Hopefully my niece will enjoy her homemade confection on her birthday .
